    <body>Converts the cursor to Bubble mode, which lets you create a callout by clicking in the frame and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a "bubble" shape is created, which consists of a rectangular or square area for holding text and a pointy area for pointing toward an area of the frame that you want to explain or emphasize. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Objects/Callouts/Adding_Callouts.htm">Adding Callouts</MadCap:xref>.</body>
